# Planning and Feature Workflow

Never generate code without understanding the project. Follow `architecture.mdc` for layer and package rules.

## AI Decision Process (mandatory before any implementation)

1. Inspect the repository tree and read existing architecture.
2. Read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` if it exists (see `graphify.mdc`).
3. Search the project for existing packages, services, repositories, and UI.
4. Identify affected packages and reusable components.
5. Produce a short implementation plan before writing code.
6. Implement following existing patterns.
7. Validate (see `testing.mdc`).
8. Refactor only if necessary to align with architecture.
9. Run tests until green.
10. Update documentation when architecture or APIs change.

## Feature Workflow (when implementing a feature)

1. Analyze requirements.
2. Create an implementation plan.
3. Identify affected modules and packages — extend existing ones when possible.
4. Implement backend (if applicable).
5. Implement shared KMP code (if applicable).
6. Implement Android/iOS Compose UI (if applicable).
7. Update Next.js (if applicable).
8. Write tests for every layer touched.
9. Run all validation commands (`testing.mdc`).
10. Fix failures and repeat until green.
11. Update documentation.
12. Summarize changes.

## Prohibited behavior

- Never guess APIs, file locations, or patterns — inspect first.
- Never create a new package without searching for an existing one to extend.
- Never skip the plan step for non-trivial work.
- Never leave TODOs unless explicitly requested.
- If multiple solutions exist, choose the one most consistent with existing architecture.
